{
  "local_port": 53302,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Applying for a driving license in Bangalore involves several steps, from gathering necessary documents to passing both written and practical tests. Below is a comprehensive guide to help you navigate the process smoothly:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Check Eligibility**\n\n- **Age Requirements:**\n  - **Motorcycle (up to 50cc):** Minimum 16 years\n  - **Motorcycle (above 50cc) and Cars (LMV):** Minimum 18 years\n  - **Commercial Vehicles:** Minimum 20 years\n\n---\n\n### **2. Gather Required Documents**\n\nEnsure you have the following documents ready:\n\n- **Proof of Age:** Aadhaar Card, Birth Certificate, Passport, Voter ID, etc.\n- **Proof of Address:** Aadhaar Card, Utility Bill, Passport, Rent Agreement, etc.\n- **Passport-size Photographs:** Generally 2-4 recent photos.\n- **Application Forms:**\n  - **Form 1:** For Learner\u2019s License\n  - **Form 4:** For Permanent Driving License\n- **Medical Certificate:** If required (typically for commercial licenses or certain age groups).\n- **Existing License:** If renewing or upgrading an old license.\n- **Vehicle Registration Certificate (if applicable):** For certain types of licenses.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Apply for a Learner\u2019s License (LL)**\n\n#### **Online Application:**\n\n1. **Visit the [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/) or [Sarathi Karnataka](https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in/) Portal:**\n   - Create an account or log in if you already have one.\n   \n2. **Fill Out the Application:**\n   - Select the option for a Learner\u2019s License.\n   - Complete the necessary details and upload required documents.\n\n3. **Pay the Application Fee:**\n   - Typically ranges between \u20b9100-\u20b9200, payable online via credit/debit card or net banking.\n\n4. **Schedule the Learner\u2019s Test:**\n   - Choose a convenient date and RTO location for your written test.\n\n#### **Offline Application:**\n\n1. **Visit the Nearest RTO Office:**\n   - Obtain and fill out **Form 2** for a Learner\u2019s License.\n\n2. **Submit Documents:**\n   - Provide all necessary documents along with passport-size photographs.\n\n3. **Pay the Fee:**\n   - Pay the required fee at the RTO.\n\n4. **Schedule the Test:**\n   - Book your written test date.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Take the Learner\u2019s Test**\n\n- **Format:** Multiple-choice questions covering traffic rules, road signs, and basic driving principles.\n- **Preparation:** Study the [Motor Vehicle Act](https://mva.gov.in/) manual or use online resources available on the Parivahan portal.\n- **Result:** Upon passing, you'll receive a Learner\u2019s License valid for 6 months.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Practice Driving**\n\n- **Duration:** Hold the Learner\u2019s License for at least 30 days before applying for the Permanent License.\n- **Guidelines:**\n  - Practice with a licensed driver (preferably an experienced driver).\n  - Familiarize yourself with different vehicle controls and traffic scenarios.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Apply for Permanent Driving License**\n\n#### **Online Application:**\n\n1. **Log in to the [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/) or [Sarathi Karnataka](https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in/) Portal:**\n   - Navigate to the Driving License section.\n\n2. **Fill Out the Application:**\n   - Complete the **Form 4** for a Permanent Driving License.\n\n3. **Upload Required Documents:**\n   - Include passport-size photographs, Learner\u2019s License, and other necessary documents.\n\n4. **Pay the Application Fee:**\n   - Typically ranges between \u20b9400-\u20b9800, depending on vehicle type and RTO.\n\n5. **Schedule the Driving Test:**\n   - Choose a date and RTO location for your practical driving test.\n\n#### **Offline Application:**\n\n1. **Visit the RTO Office:**\n   - Obtain and fill out **Form 4**.\n\n2. **Submit Documents:**\n   - Provide all necessary documents, including your Learner\u2019s License.\n\n3. **Pay the Fee:**\n   - Pay the required fee at the RTO.\n\n4. **Schedule the Test:**\n   - Book your practical driving test date.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Take the Practical Driving Test**\n\n- **Vehicle:** Use a properly registered and roadworthy vehicle.\n- **What to Expect:**\n  - Basic maneuvers such as starting, stopping, turning, reversing, and parking.\n  - Demonstration of adherence to traffic rules and safety practices.\n- **Result:** Upon passing, you'll receive your Permanent Driving License. If you fail, you'll be allowed to retake the test after a specified period.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Receive Your Driving License**\n\n- **Online Issuance:**\n  - After passing the tests, your license will be processed and available for download from the Parivahan/Sarathi portal.\n  \n- **Physical Copy:**\n  - Opt for a physical copy if available, or it will be mailed to your registered address.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Fees Overview**\n\n- **Learner\u2019s License:** \u20b9100-\u20b9200\n- **Driving Test:** \u20b9100-\u20b9200\n- **Permanent License:** \u20b9400-\u20b9800 (varies based on vehicle category)\n- **Additional Fees:** For duplicate licenses, endorsements, etc.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Tips for a Smooth Process**\n\n- **Documentation:** Double-check all documents for accuracy and completeness.\n- **Preparation:** Study the driving manual and practice extensively to increase your chances of passing the tests.\n- **Appointments:** Book appointments early to avoid delays.\n- **Vehicle Maintenance:** Ensure the vehicle used for the test is in good condition.\n\n---\n\n### **11. Contact Information**\n\n- **RTO Offices in Bangalore:**\n  - **Bangalore North RTO:** Mavalli, Bangalore\n  - **Bangalore South RTO:** Electronic City, Bangalore\n  - **Bangalore East RTO:** Indiranagar, Bangalore\n  - **Bangalore West RTO:** Rajajinagar, Bangalore\n  - *(Find your nearest RTO on the [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/) website)*\n\n- **Helpline:** \n  - **Parivahan Call Center:** 1800-4250-201\n\n- **Official Websites:**\n  - [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/)\n  - [Sarathi Karnataka](https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in/)\n  - [Karnataka Transport Department](https://transport.karnataka.gov.in/)\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps diligently, you can successfully apply for and obtain a driving license in Bangalore. Good luck!",
